and the other is the Real GDP.

161
00:07:14,145 --> 00:07:17,850
Nominal GDP shows the size of the 
economy according to today's prices.

162
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:21,254
But in real GDP, we take inflation into account.

163
00:07:21,254 --> 00:07:25,158
For example, if the nominal GDP 
growth rate of a country is 15%,

164
00:07:25,158 --> 00:07:27,893
