219
00:09:49,507 --> 00:09:52,599
that is, reducing the fiscal deficit.

220
00:09:52,599 --> 00:09:56,432
The Fiscal Deficit is the difference between 
the government's revenue and expenditure.

221
00:09:56,432 --> 00:09:58,464
The amount spent by the government

222
00:09:58,464 --> 00:10:00,311
and the revenue it earns,

223
00:10:00,311 --> 00:10:01,520
the difference between the two.

224
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:03,530
And since the word Deficit is being used here,

225
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:06,594
it means that compared to the revenue of the government,

226
00:10:06,594 --> 00:10:08,715
they are spending more than that.

227
00:10:08,715 --> 00:10:11,653
For this year, India's Fiscal Deficit is estimated to be

228
00:10:11,653 --> 00:10:14,334
₹17.86 trillion.

229
00:10:14,334 --> 00:10:18,234
But we usually look at the Fiscal Deficit 
as a percentage of GDP.

230
00:10:18,234 --> 00:10:20,374
Last year, the government had set a target that

231
00:10:20,374 --> 00:10:23,898
it should be 5.9% of GDP this year.

232
00:10:23,898 --> 00:10:25,765
And revised estimates show that

233
00:10:25,765 --> 00:10:28,121
not only has the government achieved its target

234
00:10:28,121 --> 00:10:32,287
but they have brought it down to 5.8%.

235
00:10:32,287 --> 00:10:39,366
In this year's budget, the Fiscal Deficit target 
for 2024-2025 is set at 5.1% of GDP.

236
00:10:39,366 --> 00:10:41,128
This is lower than before
which is a good thing.

237
00:10:41,128 --> 00:10:44,467
In fact, in 2003, the government had passed an Act,

238
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:47,894
