00:11:19,902 --> 00:11:25,326
Interest Servicing refers to the interest payments 
of the loan taken by the government.

254
00:11:25,326 --> 00:11:28,277
Both domestic and international 
borrowings are included in this.

255
00:11:28,277 --> 00:11:30,675
Whether the government has borrowed 
money from within the country

256
00:11:30,675 --> 00:11:33,175
or from outside the country.

257
00:11:33,528 --> 00:11:35,006
In total, this year, the government will

258
00:11:35,006 --> 00:11:39,611
spend ₹11.9 trillion on Interest Servicing.

259
00:11:39,611 --> 00:11:44,351
This number has increased by ₹1.35 trillion 
in comparison to last year.

260
00:11:44,813 --> 00:11:46,371
In this table, you can see the major expenses

261
00:11:46,371 --> 00:11:48,438
of the government based on this year's budget.

262
00:11:48,438 --> 00:11:50,467
And it has been compared to

263
00:11:50,467 --> 00:11:53,101
the revised budget estimates of last year.

264
00:11:53,101 --> 00:11:54,249
If we talk about taxes,

265
00:11:54,249 --> 00:11:56,569
there is nothing for the common people in this budget

266
00:11:56,569 --> 00:11:59,578
because nothing has changed 
in comparison to last year.

267
00:11:59,578 --> 00:12:01,080
The income tax slabs are still there.

268
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,976
But another interesting thing to see here is that

269
00:12:02,976 --> 00:12:06,944
which taxes generate the most revenue for the government?

270
00:12:07,270 --> 00:12:10,379
Budget documents show that in FY 2025,

271
00:12:10,379 --> 00:12:13,291
the government will earn 19% of its revenue

272
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:15,533
from taxes collected under the Income Tax.

273
00:12:15,533 --> 00:12:17,599
On the second number is GST with 18%.

274
00:12:17,599 --> 00:12:20,091
The government will earn 18% of its 
revenue from the taxes collected under GST.

275
00:12:20,091 --> 00:12:23,407
And then comes the Corporate Tax at 17%.

276
00:12:23,407 --> 00:12:26,214
This shows that the biggest 
contribution to the government's revenue

277
00:12:26,214 --> 00:12:27,786
is that of the Income Tax payers.

278
00:12:27,786 --> 00:12:29,946
And the GST payers.

279
00:12:29,946 --> 00:12:34,478
And the contribution of the Corporate 
Tax paid by the companies

280
00:12:34,478 --> 00:12:35,531
is lower than these.

281
00:12:35,531 --> 00:12:37,902
However, the bigger source of income for the government

282
00:12:37,902 --> 00:12:40,144
is still borrowing.

283
00:12:40,144 --> 00:12:43,150
Borrowing money is at 28%.

284
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:45,437
The Finance Minister has put a tagline for this budget,

285
00:12:45,437 --> 00:12:48,364
Viksit Bharat by 2047.
[Developed India by 2047]

286
00:12:48,364 --> 00:12:49,762
And she has also promised that

287
00:12:49,762 --> 00:12:53,778
India will become a developed nation by 2047.

288
00:12:53,778 --> 00:12:56,129
And also that by 2030,

289
00:12:56,129 --> 00:12:59,685
India will become a $7 trillion dollar economy.

290
00:12:59,685 --> 00:13:03,233
"As per the latest report by the Finance Ministry,

291
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:05,906
the Indian economy, can, of course,

292
00:13:05,906 --> 00:13:09,991
hit the, and can aspire to hit the,
$7 trillion mark by 2030."

293
00:13:09,991 --> 00:13:11,399
It sounds good to hear,

294
00:13:11,399 --> 00:13:13,008
but the reality is revealed only when

295
00:13:13,008 --> 00:13:14,676
you compare these promises

296
00:13:14,676 --> 00:13:16,839
with the promises made in the previous years.

297
00:13:16,839 --> 00:13:20,474
In the 2019 Niti Aayog meeting, PM Modi said that

298
00:13:20,474 --> 00:13:24,886
he will make India a $5 trillion economy by 2024.

299
00:13:24,886 --> 00:13:26,434
2024 is here,

300
00:13:26,434 --> 00:13:28,539
forget about the $5 trillion economy,

301
00:13:28,539 --> 00:13:31,323
India is not even a $4 trillion economy yet.

302
00:13:31,323 --> 00:13:34,577
The current status of India is a $3.7 trillion economy.

303
00:13:34,876 --> 00:13:36,127
Had the government wanted,

304
00:13:36,127 --> 00:13:39,266
they could have come up with a new 
deadline for the $5 trillion economy promise.

305
00:13:39,266 --> 00:13:40,835
Even though it didn't happen by 2024,

306
00:13:40,835 --> 00:13:43,708
they could have made 2026 or 2027 the new deadline,

307
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:46,087
but then people would have remembered that

308
00:13:46,087 --> 00:13:48,598
they had already talked about 
the $5 trillion economy previously.

309
00:13:48,598 --> 00:13:50,112
Instead, the government decided that

310
00:13:50,112 --> 00:13:51,951
this number should be pushed one step further

311
00:13:51,951 --> 00:13:55,573
and now they are promising 
a $7 trillion economy by 2030.

312
00:13:55,573 --> 00:13:57,184
By the way, I would also like to remind you that

313
00:13:57,184 --> 00:13:59,072
around 2017-18

314
00:13:59,072 --> 00:14:01,401
they were talking about a New India by 2022.

315
00:14:01,401 --> 00:14:04,972
In 2022, India's 75 years of independence was completed.

316
00:14:04,972 --> 00:14:07,868
So the government made it a deadline.

317
00:14:07,868 --> 00:14:10,049
And PM Modi had promised that

318
00:14:10,049 --> 00:14:12,628
every person, every citizen

319
00:14:12,628 --> 00:14:14,862
will have a home to live peacefully by 2022.

320
00:14:27,890 --> 00:14:30,278
It was also said that by 2022,

321
00:14:30,278 --> 00:14:31,822
farmers' income will be doubled

322
00:14:31,822 --> 00:14:34,492
and there will be bullet trains in India.

323
00:14:34,492 --> 00:14:36,373
This deadline has been pending for 2 years.

324
00:14:36,373 --> 00:14:40,074
Mark my works, when India will actually 
become a $5 trillion economy,

325
00:14:40,074 --> 00:14:42,417
which will definitely happen someday, no doubt about it,

326
00:14:42,417 --> 00:14:44,358
because there's GDP growth.

327
00:14:44,358 --> 00:14:48,206
Then you'll see how it will be 
presented as a new achievement.

328
00:14:48,206 --> 00:14:52,115
The Finance Minister focused on 
4 main sections of society in the budget.

329
00:14:52,115 --> 00:14:56,970
Poor people, women, youth, 
and the ones who feed us, the farmers.

330
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:58,789
She said that their welfare

331
00:14:58,789 --> 00:15:00,344
is the government's highest priority.

332
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:01,784
Only when they progress,

333
00:15:01,784 --> 00:15:03,354
will the country progress.

334
00:15:03,354 --> 00:15:04,590
It's absolutely correct.

335
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:05,968
But the reality is that

336
00:15:05,968 --> 00:15:09,677
India's ranking in the Hunger Index is falling.

337
00:15:09,677 --> 00:15:14,489
Today, India's ranking is 111 out of 125 on the Hunger Index

338
00:15:14,489 --> 00:15:17,394
which reveals the widespread hunger in the country.

339
00:15:17,394 --> 00:15:20,267
Youth Unemployment is at 45%

340
00:15:20,267 --> 00:15:22,766
for the ages of 20-24.

341
00:15:22,766 --> 00:15:25,412
Women's labour participation in India's workforce

342
00:15:25,412 --> 00:15:27,665
has been falling for the past few years.

343
00:15:27,665 --> 00:15:29,918
In 2005, it used to be 32%

344
00:15:29,918 --> 00:15:32,892
In 2021, it was only 19%.

345
00:15:32,892 --> 00:15:35,802
And here, the middle class is facing 
more and more difficulties.

346
00:15:35,802 --> 00:15:37,176
Look at this chart.

347
00:15:37,176 --> 00:15:40,908
This chart shows that between 2016 and 2021,

348
00:15:40,908 --> 00:15:45,707
the increase and decrease in household 
income across various sections in India.

349
00:15:45,707 --> 00:15:48,378
The richest 20% of the population of the country,

350
00:15:48,378 --> 00:15:52,561
their income has increased by a good 40%.

351
00:15:52,561 --> 00:15:56,029
And the upper middle class got some benefits too.

352
00:15:56,029 --> 00:16:01,091
But the actual middle class, lower middle 
class, and the poor people of the country,

353
00:16:01,091 --> 00:16:03,863
have seen only losses in the last few years.

354
00:16:03,863 --> 00:16:06,257
Their income has decreased.

355
00:16:06,257 --> 00:16:08,149
And the worst impact of it

356
00:16:08,149 --> 00:16:10,172
has been on the poorest 20% of the people.

357
00:16:10,172 --> 00:16:14,283
This data was published by 
India's Consumer Economy 360 survey.

358
00:16:14,283 --> 00:16:15,612
The unfortunate thing is that

359
00:16:15,612 --> 00:16:19,082
it is becoming increasingly difficult to access 
such data in the country with each day.

360
00:16:19,082 --> 00:16:23,795
Because the government simply does not 
disclose the uncomfortable data to the public.

361
00:16:23,795 --> 00:16:25,396
At the bottom of this chart it is written that,

362
00:16:25,396 --> 00:16:26,766
"Official public data on

363
00:16:26,766 --> 00:16:29,285
Indian income and consumption inequality

364
00:16:29,285 --> 00:16:31,081
has become very hard or impossible

365
00:16:31,081 --> 00:16:33,488
to be obtained in recent years."

366
00:16:33,488 --> 00:16:34,690
Look at this article from 27th March,

367
00:16:34,690 --> 00:16:37,213
the Union government has no data

368
00:16:37,213 --> 00:16:39,195
on India's offshore shell companies.

369
00:16:39,195 --> 00:16:40,905
Neither does the government have data on

370
00:16:40,905 --> 00:16:43,676
how many farmers were k!lled in the farmers' protests.

371
00:16:43,676 --> 00:16:47,020
Nor does it have data on how many 
migrants faced difficulties during COVID.

372
00:16:47,265 --> 00:16:50,090
Nor does it have data on how many 
people were k!lled in mob lynching

373
00:16:50,090 --> 00:16:53,901
nor the data on how many MSMEs 
had to be shut down during lockdown.

374
00:16:53,901 --> 00:16:57,465
This is why opposition leaders 
have often mocked the government

375
00:16:57,465 --> 00:17:00,674
saying that NDA means No Data Available.

376
00:17:00,674 --> 00:17:02,674
And the things for which 
there's some kind of data available

377
00:17:02,674 --> 00:17:03,946
it's impossible to know

378
00:17:03,946 --> 00:17:05,971
which data to trust.

379
00:17:05,971 --> 00:17:08,459
While announcing this budget, the Finance Minister said that

380
00:17:08,459 --> 00:17:10,839
in the last 10 years, the government has

381
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:13,794
assisted 250 million people to get 
freedom from multi-dimensional poverty.

382
00:17:13,794 --> 00:17:15,435
"In these 10 years,

383
00:17:15,435 --> 00:17:16,645
the Government has assisted

384
00:17:16,645 --> 00:17:19,445
25 crore people 
[250 million people]

385
00:17:19,445 --> 00:17:23,536
to get freedom from multi-dimensional poverty."

386
00:17:23,781 --> 00:17:26,623
But last year, in December, Amit Shah had said that,

387
00:17:26,623 --> 00:17:28,425
the Modi government had

388
00:17:28,425 --> 00:17:31,025
help 600 million people to be free from poverty.

389
00:17:31,025 --> 00:17:33,741
So is the 250 million number correct?

390
00:17:33,741 --> 00:17:35,357
Or the 600 million?

391
00:17:35,357 --> 00:17:36,212
No idea.

392
00:17:36,348 --> 00:17:37,925
Anyways, coming back to the budget,

393
